Certainly! NexusFlow employs custom design tokens to maintain consistency. Here’s an example of the CSS custom properties used:
css
:root {
  --primary-gradient: linear-gradient(135deg, #0ea5e9, #8b5cf6);
  --glass-effect: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.25);
  --backdrop-blur: blur(10px);
  --animation-timing: cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1);
}

These tokens define the gradient for primary elements, glass morphism effects, backdrop blurs, and animation timings, ensuring a cohesive and maintainable design system.
